22:40.776 --> 22:43.479
All right, Mrs. Sterner. 10:00.

22:44.280 --> 22:48.451
I'm sorry, honey, but the birds
will still be there next week.

22:49.118 --> 22:51.821
It's okay. I understand.

22:52.371 --> 22:54.448
I'll go fix breakfast.

23:05.009 --> 23:06.134
Chip!

23:06.135 --> 23:08.636
God! Mom, what's the matter?

23:08.637 --> 23:11.931
Oh, it's just time to get up, that's all.
I don't want you to be late for work.

23:11.932 --> 23:13.600
You scared me.

23:14.977 --> 23:16.978
Misty, honey, what's wrong?

23:16.979 --> 23:18.479
I'm stood up.

23:18.480 --> 23:20.478
I'll kill that bastard.

23:23.611 --> 23:24.861
I mean it.

23:24.862 --> 23:27.322
He should be dead,
that lousy creep.

23:27.323 --> 23:31.027
He told me he'd be here.
I'll kill him.

23:32.661 --> 23:36.741
Don't use words unless you
mean them, Misty, honey.

23:37.666 --> 23:39.584
It's him!

23:39.585 --> 23:41.378
No, no. It's the police.

23:46.842 --> 23:48.385
Good morning, Officers.

23:49.178 --> 23:51.471
Good morning, Mrs. Sutphin.

23:51.472 --> 23:54.265
Hi, Detective Pike.

23:54.266 --> 23:55.558
Morning, Misty.

23:56.560 --> 23:59.354
Mrs. Sutphin, I presume you know
about the death of Mr. Stubbins.

23:59.355 --> 24:03.776
Oh, yes, yes. A fine
man, a good teacher.

24:04.652 --> 24:08.902
Contusions, fractures, rupture
of numerous vital organs.

24:09.114 --> 24:10.573
What a mess.

24:13.535 --> 24:16.079
Oh, no, no, honey. That's Scotty.

24:16.121 --> 24:19.074
Scotty, who doesn't
wear his seatbelt.

24:20.501 --> 24:21.873
Good morning, Detectives.

24:22.503 --> 24:24.545
Nightmare on Calverton Court.

24:24.546 --> 24:26.881
The Maryland Teacher Massacre.

24:26.882 --> 24:28.584
It's not funny, son.

24:29.885 --> 24:34.135
Did you drive your car to the PTA
meeting yesterday, Mrs. Sutphin?

24:34.181 --> 24:36.349
Yes, I did.

24:36.350 --> 24:38.226
Detectives, what is this all about?

24:38.227 --> 24:40.853
I know this sounds
weird, Mr. Sutphin,

24:40.854 --> 24:44.357
but the Department of Motor Vehicles
computer shows only one blue station wagon

24:44.358 --> 24:48.111
registered to a parent of any
of Mr. Stubbins' pupils.

24:48.112 --> 24:50.780
Surely, you don't think that
Beverly was involved in this?

24:50.781 --> 24:52.073
She did it!

24:52.074 --> 24:54.575
Aimed the car right at
Mr. Stubbins and mowed him down!

24:56.412 --> 24:58.239
Shut up, Scotty.

24:59.999 --> 25:05.837
Well, as I understand it, the
only eyewitness was a drug user.

25:05.838 --> 25:09.048
I got somebody you could
run over, Mother.

25:09.049 --> 25:11.968
Misty, that's a
terrible thing to say.

25:12.177 --> 25:15.176
Detectives, it's time
for you to leave.

25:15.222 --> 25:18.349
My wife knows nothing about
this terrible accident.

25:18.350 --> 25:19.851
Murder, honey.

25:19.852 --> 25:23.312
Oh! Now here's a babe.

25:23.313 --> 25:25.641
Let's see that, young man.

25:29.611 --> 25:31.070
"P," as in...

25:31.071 --> 25:33.156
People who don't mind
their own business.

25:33.157 --> 25:35.826
Darling, it's Rosemary Ackerman's.

25:37.119 --> 25:39.662
Oh, you can tell by the
subscription label.

25:39.663 --> 25:43.291
I don't like to read about movies.
They're so violent.

25:43.292 --> 25:46.245
Besides, I always
recycle my magazines.

26:04.813 --> 26:08.316
<i>Daybreak if you wanna believe</i>

26:08.317 --> 26:12.904
<i>It can be daybreak
Ain't no time to grieve</i>

26:12.905 --> 26:17.200
<i>'Cause it's daybreak
If you'll only believe</i>

26:17.201 --> 26:21.406
<i>And let it shine, shine, shine</i>

26:51.693 --> 26:57.400
Wait for me, boys! Here! All
rinsed and ready to recycle.

26:57.574 --> 26:58.699
Morning, Mrs. Sutphin.

26:58.700 --> 27:01.577
Good morning, Gus.
Good morning, Sloppy.

27:01.578 --> 27:03.579
You know, you boys work so
hard for the environment,

27:03.580 --> 27:05.164
I thought I'd bring you something.

27:05.165 --> 27:06.958
A little drink never hurt anybody.

27:06.959 --> 27:08.786
Thank you, ma'am.

27:10.963 --> 27:13.214
Damn, that's good stuff.

27:13.215 --> 27:16.843
You believe that
goddamn litterbugger?

27:16.844 --> 27:18.761
I have told her and told her.

27:18.762 --> 27:22.390
It takes 90 to 100 years
for a tin canto decompose

27:22.391 --> 27:24.642
and she still won't recycle.

27:24.643 --> 27:27.186
It cost the taxpayers millions
of dollars last year,

27:27.187 --> 27:30.766
but she don't care nothing
about the national budget.

27:31.650 --> 27:33.234
I hate Mrs. Ackerman.

27:33.235 --> 27:34.694
I hate her, too.

27:34.695 --> 27:36.320
I hate her guts.

27:36.321 --> 27:39.491
You know, somebody
ought to kill her.

27:39.575 --> 27:41.576
Yeah.

27:41.577 --> 27:42.660
Give her a

27:43.745 --> 27:47.165
happy face, and then recycle her.

27:50.544 --> 27:53.918
For the sake of this planet,
somebody just might.

27:56.508 --> 28:00.720
But your boyfriend was convicted
of killing 12 people.

28:00.721 --> 28:01.929
I don't judge him.

28:03.015 --> 28:05.391
I just don't get it. I mean, how
can you love a mass murderer?

28:05.392 --> 28:10.063
Easy. He's handsome, he's famous
and we get conjugal visits.

28:12.399 --> 28:15.276
Serial hags. Women who
love men who mutilate.

28:15.277 --> 28:17.445
We'll be right back after
this, so please stay tuned.

28:17.446 --> 28:21.282
Turn it off. Violence is
everywhere these days.

28:21.283 --> 28:23.451
It's just Beverly.

28:23.452 --> 28:25.203
Come in, Beverly!

28:25.204 --> 28:26.996
Oh, she scared me.

28:26.997 --> 28:28.497
- Hi!
- Hi, Rosemary.

28:28.498 --> 28:29.624
Would you like a beer?

28:29.625 --> 28:32.543
Oh, no, no. Not me. Thank you.
Just a little coffee.

28:32.544 --> 28:36.088
Oh, Dottie, I'm so sorry.
I heard about your troubles.

28:36.089 --> 28:37.340
It's not fair.

28:37.341 --> 28:38.758
No.

28:39.593 --> 28:42.171
Mmm. Oh, thank you.

28:44.264 --> 28:47.141
Are those pussy willows?

28:47.142 --> 28:48.476
Dried ones.

28:48.477 --> 28:50.895
Aren't they pretty?

28:50.896 --> 28:53.224
What did you just say?

28:54.149 --> 28:57.023
Pussy willows, Dottie.

28:57.694 --> 29:00.947
Oh, my goodness!
What are you doing?

29:00.948 --> 29:02.156
I didn't do it!

29:02.157 --> 29:04.450
My Franklin Mint Fabergé egg!

29:04.451 --> 29:05.993
Dottie didn't mean to
be such a clumsy ox.

29:05.994 --> 29:07.453
You're sorry aren't you, Dottie?

29:07.454 --> 29:09.538
Rosemary, I did not break your egg!

29:09.539 --> 29:10.873
She did!

29:10.874 --> 29:13.084
Dottie, you could
at least apologize.

29:13.085 --> 29:14.752
I collect Franklin Mint!

29:14.753 --> 29:17.713
Well, we'll go right to the antique
market and we'll find you another one.

29:17.714 --> 29:21.425
Now, Misty tells me there's a whole
booth filled with Franklin Mint stuff.

29:21.426 --> 29:23.135
- But...
- Dottie, you'll lock up, won't you?

29:23.136 --> 29:25.680
- But... But...
- I'll take care of poor Rosemary.

29:25.681 --> 29:29.226
But I heard her voice. It's her!

29:38.402 --> 29:41.362
Mr. Sterner, you've
lost a tiny filling.

29:41.363 --> 29:44.490
I have to drill deeply enough
to remove all the decay.

29:44.491 --> 29:47.991
All right, go ahead, but be
careful. It really hurts.

29:49.413 --> 29:54.250
Open... Wider... Very wide.

30:06.013 --> 30:11.094
Mrs. Sterner, you can't go
back there. Mrs. Sterner...

30:11.476 --> 30:14.395
God damn you! You're trying
to hurt me on purpose.

30:14.396 --> 30:15.896
Are you okay, Ralph?

30:15.897 --> 30:18.316
Mrs. Sterner, please stay
in the waiting room.

30:18.317 --> 30:22.361
Help me, Betty, he's worse than
the dentist in The Marathon Man.

30:22.362 --> 30:23.904
I'm sorry to interrupt,
Doctor Sutphin,

30:23.905 --> 30:28.410
but there are two police detectives
waiting to see you in your office.

30:29.995 --> 30:31.447
Fine.

30:33.373 --> 30:35.750
Good morning. What is it, Officers?

30:35.751 --> 30:37.251
My patient is waiting.

30:37.252 --> 30:40.046
Doctor Sutphin, is your
wife a big reader?

30:40.047 --> 30:41.797
Bird books, mostly.

30:41.798 --> 30:43.549
Like these we found in her garbage.

30:43.550 --> 30:46.302
Urge to Kill, Mass
Murder in Houston?

30:46.303 --> 30:48.387
I'm sure those are
my son Chip's books.

30:48.388 --> 30:50.097
No, they're your wife's.

30:50.098 --> 30:51.390
We checked.

30:51.391 --> 30:54.935
She bought them at the
Browse and Learn Book Shop,

30:54.936 --> 30:56.437
along with a few other titles.

30:56.438 --> 30:59.106
Helter Skelter. Hunting Humans.

30:59.107 --> 31:04.236
MasterCard reference number
7876, dated February 5th.

31:04.237 --> 31:05.529
This is ridiculous!

31:05.947 --> 31:08.821
Doctor Sutphin, is
your wife mental?

31:12.204 --> 31:15.206
Damn these gnats. I hate them.

31:15.207 --> 31:18.331
Always something, isn't it?
Can I help you?

31:19.836 --> 31:21.629
Thanks for not buying anything.

31:21.630 --> 31:25.132
Misty, honey. Now lighten up.

31:25.133 --> 31:28.803
It's not the customer's fault
that Carl stood you up.

31:38.897 --> 31:41.982
Young man, this Fabergé
egg is chipped.

31:41.983 --> 31:43.275
Yes, ma'am, it is.

31:43.568 --> 31:45.319
I'll give you $50.

31:45.320 --> 31:48.447
That's a Franklin Mint piece. $100.

31:48.448 --> 31:53.028
$100? Franklin Mint or not,
that's damaged goods.

31:54.287 --> 31:58.583
Hello. This is a very special doll.

32:01.545 --> 32:05.795
This veil is from a gown that came from
a bride who was left at the altar.

32:05.841 --> 32:07.293
Only one of its kind.

32:11.721 --> 32:13.347
I'll take this instead.

32:13.348 --> 32:14.723
Oh, that's a nice one, huh?

32:14.724 --> 32:17.222
It'll be cold before you know it.

32:17.561 --> 32:21.561
$3? I guess that's how
I must have marked it.

32:23.400 --> 32:25.398
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

32:32.409 --> 32:34.994
Did you find your Franklin
Mint egg, Rosemary, darling?

32:34.995 --> 32:37.997
Well, I saw one, but it
was really overpriced.

32:37.998 --> 32:40.416
Oh, want me to keep this
under the table for you?

32:40.417 --> 32:43.086
If you don't mind. It was on sale.

32:47.215 --> 32:49.964
Oh, Franklin Mint.

32:57.726 --> 33:01.896
Honey, please, for
my bedroom shelf.

33:01.897 --> 33:05.067
Okay. Wrap it up for
the little lady.

33:06.735 --> 33:08.937
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

33:26.087 --> 33:27.421
I'm thirsty.

33:27.422 --> 33:28.919
What do you want?

33:40.018 --> 33:41.101
The Colts.

33:41.102 --> 33:44.146
Banner, please. Thank you.

33:46.024 --> 33:48.477
Honey, I have to take a piss.

35:29.502 --> 35:31.170
There you go.

35:31.171 --> 35:33.672
I can't believe it.
It's fucking Don Knotts.

35:33.673 --> 35:35.716
- He's the coolest. Thanks.
- Bye.

35:35.717 --> 35:39.387
Honey! Look! I made a killing.

35:52.233 --> 35:53.609
Mom, watch the booth.

35:53.610 --> 35:54.735
I want to see what's going on.

35:54.736 --> 35:56.279
Sure.

35:59.115 --> 36:01.241
I hope nothing's wrong.

36:01.242 --> 36:05.079
Beverly, honey, you've got
some doo-doo on your shoe.

36:11.127 --> 36:12.328
I hate that.

36:15.632 --> 36:17.800
There was a lady in the
men's room, I swear.

36:18.093 --> 36:20.421
A pretty little lady in the
stall right next to me.

36:37.612 --> 36:39.359
She must know him.

36:39.447 --> 36:40.648
Carl!

36:48.748 --> 36:50.916
- What happened?
- I don't know...

36:50.917 --> 36:52.664
That's $158.

36:54.254 --> 36:56.213
New York money good enough for you?

36:56.214 --> 36:57.666
Certainly.

36:59.217 --> 37:00.634
Thank you.

37:00.635 --> 37:04.385
Mother! Mother, it's Carl.

37:05.098 --> 37:06.807
He's dead.

37:06.808 --> 37:08.305
How horrible.

37:08.309 --> 37:10.644
Oh, I just sold
the Pee-Wee Herman doll.

37:10.645 --> 37:12.146
Mother, didn't you hear me?

37:12.147 --> 37:16.477
Someone murdered Carl in the men's
room. I just saw his dead body.

37:18.445 --> 37:20.647
You got your wish, dear.

37:21.156 --> 37:26.613
I didn't wish that.
I didn't want him dead.

38:22.550 --> 38:24.885
Beverly, it's me, Ted Bundy.

38:24.886 --> 38:27.554
It's late at night, six
days before my execution

38:27.555 --> 38:29.678
and it's lonely here on death row.

38:32.060 --> 38:33.811
Updating the story of the hour,

38:33.812 --> 38:36.480
the young man brutally murdered a
short time ago in the men's room

38:36.481 --> 38:38.023
of the Antique Traders Mart

38:38.024 --> 38:42.354
has been identified as 22-year-old
Carl Pageant of Towson.

39:06.094 --> 39:08.046
No, no, no! No!

39:08.096 --> 39:11.721
Chip! Our mother is Charles Manson.

39:13.518 --> 39:15.435
I'm not kidding.

39:15.436 --> 39:18.438
Carl stood me up this morning and then
he was murdered at the flea market.

39:18.439 --> 39:20.516
- Murdered?
- Yes, murdered!

39:20.525 --> 39:23.527
You said you hated your teacher
yesterday and he was murdered, too.

39:23.528 --> 39:25.863
Look, I don't know.
Maybe Mom's nuts.

39:25.864 --> 39:27.656
That's a cool idea, Misty.

39:27.657 --> 39:30.784
Hey, let's make a gore movie about
Mom, better yet, a TV series.

39:31.911 --> 39:33.078
Hey, can I borrow your mother?

39:33.079 --> 39:34.413
My aunt's coming over for dinner

39:34.414 --> 39:36.623
and she's always
getting on my nerves.

39:36.624 --> 39:37.833
My stepfather's an asshole.

39:37.834 --> 39:39.585
- She could kill him.
- How about Mrs. Ackerman?

39:39.586 --> 39:42.504
We all hate her. Who's
gonna be the next victim?

39:42.505 --> 39:45.709
No, stop it! It's not funny.

39:47.176 --> 39:51.301
Mom might do it.
Somebody else might die.

39:55.518 --> 39:57.470
Dinner is served.

39:58.813 --> 40:01.732
Let's say grace and
pray for the strength

40:01.733 --> 40:05.277
to understand the terrible
tragedies of the last few days.

40:05.278 --> 40:07.529
Amen to that.

40:07.530 --> 40:10.153
It's been a crazy day, hasn't it?

40:13.494 --> 40:16.994
Bless, O Lord, this food to our
use and our self to Thy service.

40:17.582 --> 40:19.409
- Amen.
- Amen.

40:20.960 --> 40:22.836
- Amen.
- Amen.

40:22.837 --> 40:24.338
Hungry, honey?

40:24.339 --> 40:27.674
Dottie Hinkle was right.
It is Beverly Sutphin.

40:27.675 --> 40:31.505
I tell you, I saw blood right
there on the bottom of her shoes.

40:31.638 --> 40:36.890
Not exactly blood... it was gore,
hanging there like a runny nose.

40:39.729 --> 40:42.272
Nice as pie, she was to me.
And then I hear her say it.

40:42.273 --> 40:44.146
Say what, ma'am?

40:45.109 --> 40:48.862
"Are those..." I can't
say the word out loud.

40:48.863 --> 40:51.531
Could you tell a policewoman
the exact words she used?

40:51.532 --> 40:53.029
Maybe.

40:56.162 --> 40:58.455
It's okay. Nobody's gonna hurt you.

40:58.456 --> 41:00.540
Come on. Let it out.

41:00.541 --> 41:04.166
"Pussy," that's what she
said to me. "Pussy willows."

41:10.677 --> 41:12.886
- You know, Mom...
- Mmm?

41:12.887 --> 41:15.431
Scotty thinks you're the killer.

41:17.558 --> 41:19.055
Does he?

41:19.310 --> 41:24.189
You know, for somebody who doesn't wear
his seatbelt, Scotty sure is nosy.

41:25.066 --> 41:27.234
Oh, just a second.

42:05.481 --> 42:06.728
She's gone!

42:10.236 --> 42:11.737
She's gonna kill Scotty!

42:11.738 --> 42:13.238
Get in the car, both of you.

42:13.239 --> 42:14.906
Dad, you don't think
she did it, do you?

42:14.907 --> 42:17.284
I do. Mom's gone crazy.

42:17.285 --> 42:19.953
Your mother may have some
problems. That's all, Chip.

42:19.954 --> 42:21.827
Come on, hurry.

42:43.227 --> 42:44.811
Detective Gracey and all units.

42:44.812 --> 42:47.356
Suspect's family headed
east on Calverton.

42:47.398 --> 42:49.649
Repeat, east on Calverton.

42:49.650 --> 42:51.234
Turn right on Timonium Road, Dad.

42:51.235 --> 42:53.187
- I will, I will.
- Hurry.

43:03.706 --> 43:07.542
<i>Daybreak if you'll only believe</i>

43:07.543 --> 43:12.047
<i>It can be daybreak
Ain't no time to grieve</i>

43:12.048 --> 43:15.467
<i>'Cause it's daybreak
If you'll only believe</i>

43:15.468 --> 43:19.047
<i>And let it shine, shine, shine...</i>

43:33.694 --> 43:37.273
If Mom is psycho, Scotty will
still be okay, won't he?

43:38.366 --> 43:40.575
We hope so, Son.

43:40.576 --> 43:43.780
And no matter what your mother
is, we'll love her anyway.

44:52.106 --> 44:56.186
This is Scotty's, Dad. His
parents aren't home. Come on.

44:57.612 --> 44:59.530
Scotty?

45:19.300 --> 45:21.801
What was that?

45:21.802 --> 45:23.345
I didn't hear anything.

45:23.971 --> 45:25.180
Got any dessert?

45:25.181 --> 45:28.642
Doctor Sutphin said
no sweets for you.

45:28.643 --> 45:30.477
Yeah, well, what's he know?

45:30.478 --> 45:32.476
How to send a bill!

45:38.819 --> 45:40.692
I'll get the door.

45:42.281 --> 45:43.949
Suspect's family entering house.

45:43.950 --> 45:46.368
Send backup to 400 Sycamore Street.

45:46.369 --> 45:48.287
I have a feeling old Mom's inside.

45:54.669 --> 45:59.340
Wheel of Fortune!

46:01.217 --> 46:03.635
Ralph, Wheel of Fortune's on!

46:03.636 --> 46:05.053
I'm still eating!

46:06.389 --> 46:09.263
The world's most
popular game show...

46:39.213 --> 46:43.008
Come on up, honey, before
the kids get home.

46:44.218 --> 46:45.802
May I have a "P"?

46:45.803 --> 46:47.755
Mmm-hmm. A couple of "P's."

46:53.185 --> 46:54.269
Ralph!

46:54.270 --> 46:55.854
What is it, Betty?

46:55.855 --> 46:57.773
I think we've got
mice or something.

46:58.065 --> 47:00.188
No, no, no. We paid
the exterminator.

47:14.498 --> 47:15.699
Betty?

47:25.426 --> 47:27.128
It's upstairs.

47:29.347 --> 47:31.299
I'm going in. Over.

47:35.644 --> 47:37.395
It's the door on the left.

47:42.902 --> 47:45.605
Break it down, Dad. Break it down!

47:47.698 --> 47:49.240
Scotty, man...

47:49.241 --> 47:50.818
Police! Freeze!

47:54.955 --> 47:57.829
Betty? Betty, answer me!

48:01.170 --> 48:02.872
Ralph...

48:16.560 --> 48:22.267
Help! Help me! Help me,
please! Please!

48:25.027 --> 48:26.479
Help me, somebody!

48:36.747 --> 48:39.791
Home, sweet home!
Everything's fine, kids.

48:40.167 --> 48:42.794
I can't believe I thought my
own mother was a murderess.

48:42.795 --> 48:44.921
I'm kind of disappointed she isn't.

48:44.922 --> 48:46.965
For a while there it was
like being in the movies.

48:46.966 --> 48:50.466
Anybody for dessert?
Mmm. Strawberries.

49:08.863 --> 49:10.360
Let's go.

49:42.021 --> 49:44.981
Dad, you said it would be okay.
Make them go away.

49:44.982 --> 49:46.232
This is embarrassing.

49:46.233 --> 49:47.984
Just pay no attention
to the police.

49:47.985 --> 49:49.694
It's all a terrible mistake.

49:49.695 --> 49:52.819
Do you think we'll get
on A Current Affair?

49:58.329 --> 50:02.332
Sutphin family proceeding west
on Seminary Avenue. Over.

